properties.Park: Virgin Islands Coral Reef National Monument
properties.Name: Virgin Islands Coral Reef National Monument - Hurricane Hole (No-Anchor Zone)
properties.PopupInfo:
Virgin Islands Coral Reef National Monument was created in 2001 by presidential proclamation adding 12,708 acres of submerged lands to the National Park System.

Anchoring and fishing are prohibited in Virgin Islands Coral Reef National Monument, with the exception of Blue Runner (by permit) off Cabrite Horn Point, and baitfish in Hurricane Hole (by permit).

Boaters should use moorings when visiting beaches.

White moorings are for day or night use ($26/overnight), however if marked as "day use only", overnight stay is prohibited.

Blue moorings are for commercial use only.

Orange moorings are for use while SCUBA diving (no overnight use).

Report any defects with moorings to 340-693-8950, x:240.

For more information:
Cruz Bay Visitor Center
Open Daily 8:00am to 4:30pm.
340-776-6201 x: 238

properties.Name: Virgin Islands National Park
properties.PopupInfo:
Virgin Islands National Park was established in 1956, and expanded in 1962 to include 5,560 acres of submerged land.

White moorings are for day or night use ($26/overnight), however if marked as "day use only", overnight stay is prohibited. There is a self-registration fee of $26.00 per night for overnight anchoring between the hours of 5:00 p.m. and 7:00 a.m. Golden Age/Access Passport holders pay half price.

Overnight fees must be paid prior to spending the night. Floating Fee Pay Stations are found at Leinster Bay, Francis Bay and Caneel Bay. Land-based fee stations are found at Cruz Bay Visitor Center (near the flag pole), Salt Pond Beach and on the VIERS dock in Lameshur Bay.

Larger white moorings are for vessels 61'-100'; they can be used by vessels less than 60' if vacant, but must yield use to larger vessels when approached. Smaller white moorings are for vessels less than 60'.

Blue moorings with white stripe are for Commercial Use Authorization (CUA) only. (CUA vessels have permits issued by the park.) Other vessels may use these mooring if vacant, but must yield use to CUA vessels between the hours of 8:00am - 5:00pm. Overnight use is permitted.

Orange moorings are for use while SCUBA diving (no overnight use).

Report any defects with moorings to 340-693-8950, x:241.

For more information: Cruz Bay Visitor Center
Open Daily 8:00am to 4:30pm.
340-776-6201 x: 238

properties.Name: Historic Adaptive Use Zone
properties.PopupInfo: The Historic Adaptive Use Zone includes lands and waters within one nautical mile of Garden Key and encompasses approximately 3% of the park. Recreational fishing and anchoring on sandy bottoms are allowed.

properties.Name: Research Natural Area
properties.PopupInfo:
The Dry Tortugas National Park Research Natural Area is a no-take (all forms of fishing are prohibited), no-anchoring (strategically placed mooring buoys are provided) marine reserve that was implemented to protect shallow water habitats and reef fish species.
Learn more...

properties.Name: Dry Tortugas National Park
properties.PopupInfo:
Almost 70 miles (113 km) west of Key West lies the remote Dry Tortugas National Park. The 100-square mile park is mostly open water with seven small islands. Accessible only by boat or seaplane, the park is known the world over as the home of magnificent Fort Jefferson, picturesque blue waters, superlative coral reefs and marine life, and the vast assortment of bird life that frequent the area.

All vessels must file a free boat permit at Garden Key before recreating within the park. Even if you do not plan on exploring Fort Jefferson, you must stop by Garden Key to pay the entrance fee and file the required permits. Fishermen must also file a boat permit and pay entrance fees before fishing within the park boundaries. Vessels greater than 50 meters must also obtain a Special Use Authorization in addition to the boat permit.

Vessels larger than 164 feet (50 meters) are prohibited within the park without a permit obtained from the Superintendent prior to arrival.
